Critical analysis on the quote "A person can be only born once. However,
he may die several times elsewhere''

At a basis level, this quote contrasts the physical birth of a person and 
multiple forms of death. In this quote death is not meant literal, instead
it means a person dying mentally or many emotional, psychological, or social 
deaths throughout life.

The idea of "dying several times" refers to the deep emotional pain a person
might experience throughout life. This can be caused by loss of a loved one 
betrayal or a vfery common heartbreak, but it could also be becasue of failure 
or disappointment in themselves due to past dicesions.

People change over time, this could result in losing the memory of the person
they once were. Childhood innocence is something that every person had when they 
were a child, but throughout time children lose those innocence and that results 
in dreams and ambitions being abandoned in the back of their mind never to be found 
again. When this happens people feel like their meaning in life has been lost, which
leads to major changes being made in their life.

This quote also relates to how society can erase a person in many certain ways.
A person can be erased by being excluded or rejected from people simply because 
the person dosen't fit in or they're looks aren't normal. This can casue the person's 
reputation to be lost, which can casue their mind to rethink their purpose in a such 
beautiful, but yet cruel world. Some people ignore that certain person making them
feel invisble and unreconigned by socity.

Overall the effect of this quote is strong, making us realise that people's mental
should be well kept because although you live once you can die many times in certain
ways.